. Installing SFML

Go to the SFML download page and follow the link to the latest stable version.
Download the SFML libraries for your version of Xcode and place them in a suitable location.
Use Clang for OS X 10.8 or later and GCC for older versions of Xcode.

Open the Terminal application.
The Terminal application is located in the Utilities subfolder of the Applications folder.

In the Terminal window, cd to the download location.
For example: cd Downloads

Run the install script by typing: ./install.sh followed by the Enter key.
The script will prompt you for your password and install the components correctly.

More Information: http://www.cprogramming.com/xcode.html

SFML and Xcode (Mac OS X):https://developer.apple.com/library/ios/technotes/tn2339/_index.html
